properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued February 12 at 1:39PM MST until February 15 at 7:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 35 to 40 mph with gusts up to 60 mph
possible.

* WHERE...Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County,
North Snowy Range Foothills, South Laramie Range and South
Laramie Range Foothills Counties.

* WHEN...From Friday morning through Saturday evening.

* IMPACTS...High risk for blowovers. Travel could be difficult
especially for lightweight, high profile vehicles and campers.
properties.instruction:
Call 511 or go to wyoroad.info for the latest road conditions and
closures.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM FRIDAY MORNING THROUGH SATURDAY EVENING
